==English==

===Pronunciation===
'''Cy*ber-space'''
SA&Iuml;-buhr-spe&iuml;s

===Etymology===
A [[portmanteau]] of [[cybernetics]] and [[space]].
Coined by novelist William Gibson in his 1982 novel "Necromancer".

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''cyberspace'''
#A [[world]] of [[information]] through the [[Internet]].
#(''science fiction'') A [[three-dimensional]] [[representation]] of [[virtual space]] in a [[computer network]].

